The paper deals with tensor decompositions, which are commonly used in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the challenges of big data analytics, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The proposed algorithms involve compression and distributed computing, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
